The paper deals with unsupervised neural machine translation, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP) and computational linguistics (CL). The proposed method utilizes images for disambiguation, which suggests the involvement of computer vision (CV) techniques. The framework is based on machine learning (LG) and involves bidirectional translation, which is a common topic in artificial intelligence (AI). Finally, the paper focuses on multi-modal translation, which involves both text and images, and thus falls under the category of multimedia (MM).
